Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Investigation Agency has seized at the 
Lahore railway station 92 kg of acetic anhydride sent by Indian 
intelligence for manufacture of narcotics in the tribal areas. 
This was stated by the interior minister, retired Major General 
Nasirullah Khan Babar, at a news conference in Islamabad today. 
He said the carrier of the drug, Mohammad Imran, a Pakistani 
who was guest of Indian intelligence agency in Amritsar, has 
been arrested along with the chemical. The interior minister 
asked the international community to take notice of the Indian 
activities of encouraging the manufacture of heroin in Pakistan. 

